WEBVTT

00:05.965 --> 00:07.967
♪ ♪

00:19.603 --> 00:21.063
[sighs softly]

00:22.773 --> 00:24.900
[Jeremiah] Morning, Bells.

00:26.527 --> 00:28.779
Jeremiah, what are you...

00:37.037 --> 00:39.039
Wait, Conrad, what are...

00:39.039 --> 00:40.791
It's okay.

00:42.877 --> 00:45.212
You and I are meant to be.

00:46.672 --> 00:47.673
[Jeremiah] Belly, wait.

00:47.673 --> 00:50.593
It's always been us.

00:50.593 --> 00:52.261
How can you not see?

00:58.184 --> 01:01.312
[Belly] Even my dream life
is complicated.

01:01.312 --> 01:02.521
[sighs]

01:07.359 --> 01:10.112
The truth is, everything's
gotten more complicated

01:10.112 --> 01:11.363
ever since that kiss.

01:11.363 --> 01:13.491
A kiss I can't stop
thinking about.

01:13.491 --> 01:16.160
A kiss that's literally
invading my dreams.

01:16.160 --> 01:17.995
It's invading everything.

01:19.038 --> 01:20.873
[squawking]

01:24.251 --> 01:25.753
Morning.

01:26.795 --> 01:28.631
Morning, hon.
Hey, do you have a second?

01:28.631 --> 01:29.757
Yeah.

01:29.757 --> 01:31.634
Cleveland just called.
I got to go...

01:32.676 --> 01:35.095
It'll just take a sec.

01:35.095 --> 01:40.100
I want you to ask Belly to be
her escort to the deb ball.

01:40.100 --> 01:41.769
Mom, I can't.

01:41.769 --> 01:43.437
Why not?

01:43.437 --> 01:45.815
Just tell Jeremiah to ask her.

01:45.815 --> 01:48.442
Connie, you know how much
it'll mean to her if it's you.

01:48.442 --> 01:49.944
You're her Prince Charming,
and we all know it.

01:49.944 --> 01:51.654
No, that's not...

01:51.654 --> 01:53.155
You've always been
so good to her.

01:53.155 --> 01:54.532
Remember when
you were the only one

01:54.532 --> 01:56.450
who'd let her tag after
you and the boys?

01:56.450 --> 01:59.703
I just, uh... I want it
to go perfectly for her.

01:59.703 --> 02:01.038
Please?

02:01.038 --> 02:02.748
For me?

02:02.748 --> 02:04.375
I'll think about it.

02:04.375 --> 02:05.751
Okay, that's my Connie.

02:05.751 --> 02:07.211
I didn't say I would do it.

02:07.211 --> 02:09.045
Oh, and don't be late this
afternoon for the tournament

02:09.045 --> 02:10.297
'cause we need help setting up.

02:10.297 --> 02:13.008
- I know. I know.
- Play It Forward!

02:13.008 --> 02:14.844
[Conrad] Play It Forward.

02:14.844 --> 02:17.137
Uh, you know, it's, uh,
not too late to sign up.

02:17.137 --> 02:19.390
Mom, no.

02:19.390 --> 02:21.183
Maybe.

02:24.353 --> 02:25.603
- Oh.
- Oh, sorry, um...

02:25.603 --> 02:26.689
Uh, morning.

02:26.689 --> 02:28.190
- Hi.
- [door closes]

02:28.190 --> 02:29.567
- How'd you sleep?
- Fine.

02:29.567 --> 02:30.693
Great.

02:30.693 --> 02:32.027
[chuckles] No dreams.

02:32.027 --> 02:33.195
[Steven] Excuse me.

02:33.195 --> 02:36.031
Excuse me, excuse me, excuse me.

02:36.031 --> 02:37.116
[door closes]

02:37.116 --> 02:38.534
[Jeremiah] Hey, um,

02:38.534 --> 02:40.327
you excited about
the volleyball tournament today?

02:40.327 --> 02:41.996
[Steven] Belly!

02:43.414 --> 02:45.416
Why do you keep leaving
your hair on the shower wall?

02:45.416 --> 02:47.751
- Calm down.
- No. It is gross.

02:47.751 --> 02:50.296
All right? If you do it again,
I'm leaving it on your pillow.

02:50.296 --> 02:52.131
Steven!

02:53.173 --> 02:55.301
I, uh, I didn't want
to rush you or anything,

02:55.301 --> 02:56.927
but I would like to eventually

02:56.927 --> 02:58.929
talk about what happened
the other night.

02:58.929 --> 03:00.347
Y... uh, yeah, no, I mean...

03:00.347 --> 03:02.600
But, uh, you know, with-with
Taylor coming into town

03:02.600 --> 03:04.476
and the tournament
and everything...

03:04.476 --> 03:06.312
- Gotcha. Yeah.
Maybe after everything's...
- Yeah.

03:06.312 --> 03:08.355
- [chuckles] Yeah.
Sounds-sounds good.
- [chuckles]

03:08.355 --> 03:09.857
- Okay.
- Great.

03:11.859 --> 03:13.319
Okay.

03:13.319 --> 03:15.571
Uh, I'm gonna... go get dressed.

03:15.571 --> 03:17.156
I think your mom's
waiting for me.

03:17.156 --> 03:19.366
- Yeah, yeah. See ya.
- [chuckles]

03:22.953 --> 03:24.622
[Conrad sighs]

03:24.622 --> 03:26.290
Yeah, it's wood rot.

03:26.290 --> 03:28.751
Yeah, see how brittle it is
on the inside?

03:28.751 --> 03:30.127
God, this is bad, man.

03:30.127 --> 03:31.921
We have to pry off bits
until we reach clean wood.

03:31.921 --> 03:33.088
[Cleveland sighs]

03:34.715 --> 03:36.050
Fuck! Ow.

03:36.050 --> 03:37.676
You're a little on edge,
my friend.

03:37.676 --> 03:39.219
It's been a bad week.

03:39.219 --> 03:40.429
Is your dad back in town?

03:40.429 --> 03:42.305
No, other stuff.

03:42.305 --> 03:43.766
How are things looking
with that girl?

03:43.766 --> 03:45.392
Not good.

03:45.392 --> 03:46.560
- [grunts]
- [wood snaps]

03:46.560 --> 03:48.687
And this isn't
looking good either, man.

03:48.687 --> 03:50.397
I mean, it just keeps
going and going.

03:50.397 --> 03:52.650
The whole goddamn thing is
infected, and I didn't notice.

03:52.650 --> 03:54.109
It's everywhere,
and I didn't notice!

03:54.109 --> 03:55.861
Conrad, whoa! Whoa.

03:55.861 --> 03:58.364
- What is going on, man?
- [sighs]

03:58.364 --> 04:00.741
My heart's beating
really fast, and, um...

04:00.741 --> 04:02.368
[wheezing gasp]

04:02.368 --> 04:03.577
[sniffles]

04:03.577 --> 04:05.537
[whispers] It's really
hard to breathe.

04:05.537 --> 04:07.081
Hey.

04:09.833 --> 04:12.252
No, it's normal.
You're having a panic attack.

04:12.252 --> 04:14.046
It's okay.

04:14.046 --> 04:15.839
Okay, you look at me.

04:15.839 --> 04:16.882
Deep breaths.

04:16.882 --> 04:18.591
Okay?

04:18.591 --> 04:20.844
In. [inhales]

04:20.844 --> 04:22.471
Out. [exhales]

04:22.471 --> 04:23.764
In.

04:25.140 --> 04:26.600
Out.

04:26.600 --> 04:27.768
In.

04:29.144 --> 04:30.479
Out.

04:31.855 --> 04:33.399
Let it out, man.

04:35.401 --> 04:37.945
Conrad, what's going on?

04:47.913 --> 04:50.165
It's my mom. She...

04:57.089 --> 04:59.174
Everything okay?

04:59.174 --> 05:02.177
Yeah. It's just hot today.

05:02.177 --> 05:03.846
Just a little longer.

05:04.888 --> 05:06.348
[sighs]

05:06.348 --> 05:08.642
Don't you just love that dress?
[chuckles]

05:08.642 --> 05:10.686
[sighs softly]

05:10.686 --> 05:12.855
Yeah, I love it.

05:12.855 --> 05:15.691
You excited for
the volleyball tournament?

05:15.691 --> 05:17.359
Yeah, I can't wait.

05:17.359 --> 05:20.487
I-I want to raise
the most money of anyone.

05:20.487 --> 05:22.906
Mm, Steven's the only one
I'm worried about.

05:22.906 --> 05:24.950
And which charity
are you representing?

05:24.950 --> 05:26.869
The one you help with.

05:26.869 --> 05:28.370
The homeless women's shelter.

05:28.370 --> 05:29.621
[chuckles softly]

05:29.621 --> 05:31.081
That's sweet.

05:31.081 --> 05:32.249
Thank you, Belly.

05:33.834 --> 05:35.627
Uh, sit still.

05:35.627 --> 05:38.088
I just need a couple more
seconds with those frills.

05:42.301 --> 05:46.305
There's a breathing technique
for anxiety attacks.

05:46.305 --> 05:48.390
Four seconds inhale
through your nose,

05:48.390 --> 05:51.894
seven to hold, eight to exhale.

05:51.894 --> 05:54.521
How do you know all this stuff?

05:54.521 --> 05:56.482
It was when
my second book came out.

05:56.482 --> 05:59.401
That's when I had my first
full-blown panic attack.

05:59.401 --> 06:01.737
I went to the E.R. thinking
I was having a heart attack.

06:01.737 --> 06:04.782
[chuckles] Learned
coping methods after that.

06:04.782 --> 06:05.949
Wow.

06:09.703 --> 06:12.581
Maybe you should
tell your mom you know.

06:12.581 --> 06:13.582
Yeah, I know.

06:13.582 --> 06:15.667
I want to. I swear.

06:15.667 --> 06:17.961
But every time I try,
I don't know how.

06:19.421 --> 06:22.007
I mean, she doesn't want me
or my brother to know.

06:22.007 --> 06:24.635
Finding out would crush her.
It would ruin everything.

06:28.180 --> 06:32.183
I feel like maybe if-if I...

06:32.183 --> 06:34.603
I just keep it inside,
you know...

06:39.191 --> 06:41.693
...maybe that's
what keeps her alive.

06:44.822 --> 06:46.782
You're afraid
to step on a crack.

06:46.782 --> 06:49.743
You're afraid that you'll be
the one to make it real.

06:52.412 --> 06:54.832
This isn't something
you can control.

06:55.832 --> 06:59.920
This is happening whether
you say it out loud or not.

06:59.920 --> 07:04.341
Conrad, it's not on you.

07:04.341 --> 07:05.926
Okay?

07:14.726 --> 07:16.436
It's not on me.

07:23.735 --> 07:25.904
Hey, Belly.

07:25.904 --> 07:27.531
Oh, hey.

07:27.531 --> 07:29.199
What's that?

07:29.199 --> 07:31.994
- My secret weapon.
- Hmm.

07:31.994 --> 07:34.121
Feeling good
about the tournament?

07:34.121 --> 07:35.873
Yeah, I'm ready.

07:35.873 --> 07:38.375
If you stay ready,
you won't have to get ready.

07:39.376 --> 07:41.003
[chuckles softly]

07:41.003 --> 07:42.504
Mm.

07:42.504 --> 07:44.256
- That was cheesy.
- Yeah.

07:44.256 --> 07:45.924
You try, you try coming up with

07:45.924 --> 07:47.759
a motivational phrase
with no cheese.

07:47.759 --> 07:50.179
[clicks tongue] Hmm.
I'm thinking.

07:51.889 --> 07:53.307
- [chuckles]
- I'm thinking.

07:53.307 --> 07:54.600
[laughs]

07:54.600 --> 07:56.018
Belly?

07:56.018 --> 07:57.644
Yeah?

07:58.979 --> 08:00.772
I'm sorry.

08:00.772 --> 08:02.566
For being cheesy?

08:03.984 --> 08:05.819
For being a jerk the other day

08:05.819 --> 08:07.696
and pretending like
I don't remember

08:07.696 --> 08:10.240
when I remember everything.

08:10.240 --> 08:13.285
I just keep replaying it
over and over again in my head.

08:14.828 --> 08:16.538
I-I don't know what to say.

08:16.538 --> 08:18.081
I know.

08:18.081 --> 08:19.750
It's too little, too late.
I get it.

08:19.750 --> 08:21.126
Um...

08:25.297 --> 08:27.466
Can I take you to the ball?

08:30.219 --> 08:31.511
What?

08:31.511 --> 08:33.513
I mean, I already know
all the dances.

08:33.513 --> 08:35.349
It's no problem.

08:37.142 --> 08:38.143
[doorbell rings]

08:38.143 --> 08:39.727
Uh, I'll-I'll think about it.

08:39.727 --> 08:41.020
Think about it.

08:43.982 --> 08:47.027
What have you gotten yourself
into, Cinderbelly?

08:47.027 --> 08:49.112
- Oh, I'm so happy you're here.
- [sighs heavily]

08:49.112 --> 08:50.739
- Where's my shirt, okay?
- [chuckles]

08:50.739 --> 08:52.282
We're gonna kick
all of their asses.

08:52.282 --> 08:54.076
[whispers] Yeah. Let's go.

08:54.076 --> 08:55.869
[exhales softly]

08:55.869 --> 08:57.162
[door closes]

08:58.413 --> 09:00.415
- What's up, Taylor?
- Hey.

09:03.752 --> 09:06.255
[quietly] What's the latest
with you two?

09:06.255 --> 09:08.257
There's so much to go over.

09:10.133 --> 09:11.718
You are kidding me.

09:11.718 --> 09:12.928
Dead serious.

09:12.928 --> 09:14.721
Was he cool about it
or was he nervous?

09:14.721 --> 09:15.931
Or was he, like, begging?

09:15.931 --> 09:17.474
Oh, my God, please tell me
he was begging.

09:17.474 --> 09:20.352
He was not begging.

09:20.352 --> 09:22.020
But he was
kind of nervous, though.

09:22.020 --> 09:23.981
This just makes things
all the more exciting

09:23.981 --> 09:26.233
because you get to tell him no.

09:26.233 --> 09:28.527
- [♪ Solange: "Losing You"]
- ♪ I know you're waiting ♪

09:28.527 --> 09:31.488
♪ For the words
that you can't get from me ♪

09:31.488 --> 09:32.823
♪ Just treat me good
and, baby...

09:32.823 --> 09:35.158
Belly, you are
telling him no, okay?

09:35.158 --> 09:36.618
Because need not I remind you

09:36.618 --> 09:38.453
of the bullshit
Conrad pulled last week.

09:38.453 --> 09:40.998
- Yeah, I know, I know.
- Need not I also remind you

09:40.998 --> 09:43.875
of the emotionally available,
fun, sweet,

09:43.875 --> 09:45.544
better-looking brother

09:45.544 --> 09:47.629
who is at your feet
right now waiting for you.

09:47.629 --> 09:48.714
[knocking on door]

09:48.714 --> 09:50.674
Are you girls ready?
I'm gonna take you over.

09:50.674 --> 09:52.175
[gasps] Oh, can I drive?

09:52.175 --> 09:53.385
[gasps] No.

09:54.386 --> 09:56.138
[scoffs]

09:56.138 --> 09:59.433
Look, we don't have to talk
about this right now.

09:59.433 --> 10:01.810
- This is not why you came.
- This is exactly why I came.

10:01.810 --> 10:04.479
I'm just glad you're here
so we can win this tournament.

10:04.479 --> 10:06.481
No. You're glad I'm here because

10:06.481 --> 10:08.025
I'm about to get you
on Team Jeremiah,

10:08.025 --> 10:10.777
which I'm the very
enthusiastic CEO of, so...

10:10.777 --> 10:12.654
[chuckles softly]

10:12.654 --> 10:15.032
♪ Am I losing you for good...

10:15.032 --> 10:17.409
[sighs] Oh, yeah. We're ready.

10:17.409 --> 10:19.244
- [♪ HAIM: "Now I'm In It"]
- [grunts]

10:19.244 --> 10:20.454
♪ I'm alone in my head...

10:20.454 --> 10:22.247
- Good job.
- [exhales sharply]

10:22.247 --> 10:24.291
♪ Can't get a read on myself ♪

10:24.291 --> 10:25.292
♪ Gotta change...

10:25.292 --> 10:26.626
I like your visors.

10:26.626 --> 10:28.879
Oh, thanks.
We got them this morning.

10:28.879 --> 10:30.589
Steven insisted on the green

10:30.589 --> 10:32.966
- because he says
it makes our eyes pop.
- [chuckles] Yeah.

10:32.966 --> 10:35.385
Yeah, they're really poppin'.

10:35.385 --> 10:37.721
♪ We cannot be friends...

10:37.721 --> 10:39.306
Yeah.

10:39.306 --> 10:41.808
Uh, so how long
you in town for, Taylor?

10:41.808 --> 10:44.478
I don't know.
I'm just gonna play it by ear.

10:44.478 --> 10:46.396
♪ 'Cause now I'm in it ♪

10:46.396 --> 10:48.857
♪ But I've been trying
to find my way back...

10:48.857 --> 10:50.567
Well, it was great
to finally meet you.

10:50.567 --> 10:52.402
I'm glad to put a face
to the name.

10:52.402 --> 10:54.488
Yeah.

10:54.488 --> 10:55.989
I'm gonna go put on
some sunscreen.

10:55.989 --> 10:57.407
Uh, yeah, okay.

10:57.407 --> 10:59.743
♪ Find my way back
for a minute...

11:02.496 --> 11:04.498
You guys look good together.

11:04.498 --> 11:05.791
Oh, you think so?

11:05.791 --> 11:07.334
It's cute. Okay.

11:07.334 --> 11:09.044
See you on the court.

11:09.044 --> 11:11.797
♪ And the rain
keeps coming down...

11:11.797 --> 11:13.548
[Susannah] Good afternoon.

11:13.548 --> 11:15.092
I'm Susannah Fisher...

11:15.092 --> 11:16.635
- [scattered cheers]
- ...chair of the club's

11:16.635 --> 11:18.720
community service board,
and I am delighted

11:18.720 --> 11:21.348
to welcome you
to Play It Forward!

11:21.348 --> 11:23.225
- [cheering]
- [whoops]

11:23.225 --> 11:26.103
You know, as my mother
used to say,

11:26.103 --> 11:29.689
if you're lucky enough to be at
the beach, you're lucky enough.

11:29.689 --> 11:32.317
And we are
very fortunate indeed...

11:32.317 --> 11:34.319
- Hey.
- ...which is why,
in the spirit of fun

11:34.319 --> 11:36.822
- and friendly competition...
- [indistinct chatter]
- Hey.

11:36.822 --> 11:38.782
...it is time to open
our hearts and our wallets

11:38.782 --> 11:41.076
and give back to those
who may not be as fortunate.

11:41.076 --> 11:44.413
We have teams raising money
for homelessness,

11:44.413 --> 11:46.206
women's shelters,
environmental causes

11:46.206 --> 11:48.500
and many more.

11:48.500 --> 11:51.420
And Play It Forward
will match pledges

11:51.420 --> 11:53.630
for the winner
of the tournament!

11:53.630 --> 11:56.258
[cheering]

11:56.258 --> 12:00.303
Pledge tables still open,
so please donate generously.

12:00.303 --> 12:03.890
And with that,
I say let the games begin!

12:03.890 --> 12:06.017
[cheering]

12:06.017 --> 12:08.019
[man] Let's get started!

12:08.019 --> 12:10.230
That trophy is going to be mine.

12:10.230 --> 12:12.816
Watch out for those two.

12:12.816 --> 12:14.526
Her spike is lethal.

12:15.527 --> 12:16.653
Let's do this.

12:20.449 --> 12:21.450
[sighs]

12:22.451 --> 12:23.910
[Taylor] Hi.

12:24.911 --> 12:26.371
Looking good, Jeremy.

12:26.371 --> 12:28.123
What's up, Taylor?

12:28.123 --> 12:30.667
[laughter, indistinct chatter]

12:33.128 --> 12:34.963
Oh, please. Don't even sweat it.

12:34.963 --> 12:36.339
He's in the rearview.

12:36.339 --> 12:38.091
You sure about that?

12:39.676 --> 12:42.345
Yeah, I'm Team Jelly.
I've got your back.

12:42.345 --> 12:43.638
Okay?

12:43.638 --> 12:45.015
Thanks.

12:52.189 --> 12:54.524
- Hey.
- Hey.

12:54.524 --> 12:56.818
Um...

12:56.818 --> 12:59.029
So, uh, just a heads-up.

12:59.029 --> 13:00.780
My mom is kind of freaking out

13:00.780 --> 13:03.200
because Belly doesn't have
an escort to this dance.

13:03.200 --> 13:04.534
[Nicole] She's right.

13:04.534 --> 13:06.745
She needs to hurry up
and decide.

13:06.745 --> 13:08.622
The thing is, she kind of...

13:08.622 --> 13:11.833
My mom asked me
to-to take Belly.

13:11.833 --> 13:13.627
Why doesn't she just go
with Jeremiah?

13:13.627 --> 13:15.420
Yeah.

13:15.420 --> 13:17.255
I mean... you know Jere.

13:17.255 --> 13:20.008
He, like, he hates
this kind of a thing.

13:20.008 --> 13:22.469
Um, and plus,
I already know the dances.

13:22.469 --> 13:24.095
Yeah. No, I remember.

13:24.095 --> 13:26.014
You're very good at the dances.

13:26.014 --> 13:27.641
Don't forget it.

13:27.641 --> 13:29.935
[laughs] I won't.

13:29.935 --> 13:31.102
You want a drink?

13:31.102 --> 13:32.187
- Sure.
- Gotcha.

13:34.689 --> 13:37.150
[applause, cheering]

13:38.401 --> 13:40.695
- [♪ M.I.A.: "Bad Girls"]
- Okay. Let's do it.

13:42.072 --> 13:44.032
[Conrad] Let's go, Belly!
Come on!

13:44.032 --> 13:45.033
Yeah!

13:45.033 --> 13:47.160
[both] Play sharp, play smart.

13:47.160 --> 13:49.746
- [whistle blows]
- ♪ Live fast, die young...

13:49.746 --> 13:51.540
- [Conrad] Good job, Belly!
- Ready?

13:51.540 --> 13:52.790
[Conrad] You got it, you got it!

13:52.790 --> 13:54.292
- Yeah!
- Nice.

13:54.292 --> 13:57.003
- [cheering]
- ♪ Live fast, die young ♪

13:57.003 --> 13:58.296
♪ Bad girls do it well ♪

13:58.296 --> 13:59.548
♪ Live fast, die young ♪

13:59.548 --> 14:01.758
♪ Bad girls do it well ♪

14:01.758 --> 14:03.301
♪ Get back, get down ♪

14:03.301 --> 14:04.636
Go, Belly.

14:04.636 --> 14:05.971
♪ Pull me closer...

